      "resolution_level": 4,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_biology_l3_vaccination_principles",
      "content": {
        "title": "Herd Immunity and Coverage Thresholds",
        "definition": "Population-level protection when sufficient immunized individuals interrupt pathogen transmission, protecting unvaccinated vulnerable members.",
        "summary": "Threshold depends on R0: higher transmissibility requires higher coverage. Herd immunity reduces outbreak size."
