      "resolution_level": 4,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_biology_l3_vaccination_principles",
      "content": {
        "title": "Vaccine Adverse Events and Contraindications",
        "definition": "Expected local and systemic reactogenicity versus rare serious adverse events, with absolute and relative contraindications guiding safe immunization.",
        "summary": "Most reactions are mild (soreness, fever). Anaphylaxis is rare. Live vaccines avoided in severe immunodeficiency and pregnancy."
      },
