      "resolution_level": 4,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_biology_l3_vaccination_principles",
      "content": {
        "title": "Vaccine Types",
        "definition": "Classification of vaccines including live attenuated, inactivated, subunit, conjugate, and nucleic acid platforms differing in immunogenicity and safety profiles.",
        "summary": "Live attenuated vaccines mimic natural infection with strong memory but contraindications in immunocompromised hosts. Inactivated and subunit vaccines are safer but often require adjuvants and boosters."
