      "id": "spine_biology_l5_booster_dose_rationale",
      "resolution_level": 5,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_biology_l3_vaccination_principles",
      "content": {
        "title": "Booster Dose Rationale",
        "definition": "Additional vaccine doses re-stimulating memory lymphocytes to increase antibody titer, affinity, and duration of protection.",
        "summary": "Primary series establishes memory; boosters expand clone size and drive affinity maturation. Waning immunity necessitates periodic boosters."
      },
